[
  {
    "text": "Do you want your multicloud",
    "start": "270",
    "end": "1379"
  },
  {
    "text": "deployments to be boring",
    "start": "1380",
    "end": "3299"
  },
  {
    "text": "or like a roller coaster?",
    "start": "3300",
    "end": "4499"
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm Chris Lazzaro from IBM,",
    "start": "6150",
    "end": "8069"
  },
  {
    "text": "and I'm going to talk to you about",
    "start": "8070",
    "end": "9868"
  },
  {
    "text": "GitOps.",
    "start": "9870",
    "end": "10870"
  },
  {
    "text": "for multicloud.",
    "start": "13730",
    "end": "14730"
  },
  {
    "text": "But before I do that, please be sure",
    "start": "18530",
    "end": "20239"
  },
  {
    "text": "to like and subscribe.",
    "start": "20240",
    "end": "21260"
  },
  {
    "text": "The approach we're going to talk",
    "start": "22640",
    "end": "23959"
  },
  {
    "text": "about today is simple.",
    "start": "23960",
    "end": "25429"
  },
  {
    "text": "Consistent.",
    "start": "28900",
    "end": "29900"
  },
  {
    "text": "And secure.",
    "start": "34270",
    "end": "35270"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, typically, when",
    "start": "39510",
    "end": "41340"
  },
  {
    "text": "customers are building applications,",
    "start": "42510",
    "end": "44819"
  },
  {
    "text": "they start out with an on-prem",
    "start": "44820",
    "end": "46559"
  },
  {
    "text": "environment.",
    "start": "46560",
    "end": "47560"
  },
  {
    "text": "And they have a GUI and a CLI",
    "start": "51380",
    "end": "53839"
  },
  {
    "text": "for managing that environment.",
    "start": "53840",
    "end": "56029"
  },
  {
    "text": "But then they want to move to the",
    "start": "61770",
    "end": "63509"
  },
  {
    "text": "cloud and utilize cloud",
    "start": "63510",
    "end": "64828"
  },
  {
    "text": "environments, so they start using",
    "start": "64830",
    "end": "67139"
  },
  {
    "text": "a cloud.",
    "start": "67140",
    "end": "68140"
  },
  {
    "text": "And it has its own GUI",
    "start": "68930",
    "end": "71389"
  },
  {
    "text": "and its own CLI,",
    "start": "71390",
    "end": "73429"
  },
  {
    "text": "and things get a little bit more",
    "start": "73430",
    "end": "74599"
  },
  {
    "text": "complicated.",
    "start": "74600",
    "end": "75919"
  },
  {
    "text": "And now they have hybrid cloud apps",
    "start": "75920",
    "end": "77929"
  },
  {
    "text": "that are stretching across on-prem",
    "start": "77930",
    "end": "79639"
  },
  {
    "text": "and cloud.",
    "start": "79640",
    "end": "80868"
  },
  {
    "text": "And these different environments",
    "start": "80870",
    "end": "82879"
  },
  {
    "text": "can be difficult to manage.",
    "start": "82880",
    "end": "84349"
  },
  {
    "text": "But the advantages of cloud are",
    "start": "85620",
    "end": "87089"
  },
  {
    "text": "there, and so they continue,",
    "start": "87090",
    "end": "89188"
  },
  {
    "text": "and now they add additional",
    "start": "89190",
    "end": "91049"
  },
  {
    "text": "clouds in",
    "start": "91050",
    "end": "92969"
  },
  {
    "text": "order to have the flexibility",
    "start": "92970",
    "end": "94799"
  },
  {
    "text": "to move their applications",
    "start": "94800",
    "end": "96629"
  },
  {
    "text": "from one cloud to the next or use",
    "start": "96630",
    "end": "99148"
  },
  {
    "text": "multiple clouds for different",
    "start": "99150",
    "end": "100349"
  },
  {
    "text": "purposes.",
    "start": "100350",
    "end": "101819"
  },
  {
    "text": "So now you've had a GUI and CLI",
    "start": "101820",
    "end": "104251"
  },
  {
    "text": "across your on-prem,",
    "start": "104251",
    "end": "105779"
  },
  {
    "text": "your first cloud and any other cloud",
    "start": "105780",
    "end": "107429"
  },
  {
    "text": "that you're using, and things",
    "start": "107430",
    "end": "109499"
  },
  {
    "text": "start to become pretty difficult.",
    "start": "109500",
    "end": "111480"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, OpenShift helps.",
    "start": "112600",
    "end": "114310"
  },
  {
    "text": "OpenShift provides a secure,",
    "start": "117260",
    "end": "119329"
  },
  {
    "text": "consistent way of managing",
    "start": "119330",
    "end": "121969"
  },
  {
    "text": "your infrastructure and",
    "start": "121970",
    "end": "123109"
  },
  {
    "text": "applications.",
    "start": "123110",
    "end": "124489"
  },
  {
    "text": "No matter whether they're on-prem",
    "start": "124490",
    "end": "126379"
  },
  {
    "text": "or in the cloud.",
    "start": "126380",
    "end": "127380"
  },
  {
    "text": "But we're going to take things a",
    "start": "128509",
    "end": "129619"
  },
  {
    "text": "step further and show how GitOps",
    "start": "129620",
    "end": "132948"
  },
  {
    "text": "can really manage everything",
    "start": "132950",
    "end": "134959"
  },
  {
    "text": "through Git operations.",
    "start": "134960",
    "end": "136310"
  },
  {
    "text": "So you have your Dev team.",
    "start": "137940",
    "end": "139560"
  },
  {
    "text": "And they are used to",
    "start": "142100",
    "end": "143929"
  },
  {
    "text": "doing all of their work inside of",
    "start": "143930",
    "end": "145538"
  },
  {
    "text": "Git. So source code is all managed",
    "start": "145540",
    "end": "147918"
  },
  {
    "text": "within Git.",
    "start": "147920",
    "end": "148920"
  },
  {
    "text": "And you have your Ops team.",
    "start": "149640",
    "end": "150930"
  },
  {
    "text": "And they're in charge of managing",
    "start": "153090",
    "end": "154679"
  },
  {
    "text": "all of your different environments.",
    "start": "154680",
    "end": "156058"
  },
  {
    "text": "So how do we bring Dev and Ops",
    "start": "157750",
    "end": "159849"
  },
  {
    "text": "together?",
    "start": "159850",
    "end": "160850"
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, we can set up repositories",
    "start": "162530",
    "end": "165169"
  },
  {
    "text": "for infrastructure.",
    "start": "165170",
    "end": "166170"
  },
  {
    "text": "For services.",
    "start": "168950",
    "end": "169950"
  },
  {
    "text": "And for the applications.",
    "start": "173760",
    "end": "175049"
  },
  {
    "text": "So when we go and look at your",
    "start": "177690",
    "end": "179069"
  },
  {
    "text": "deployed environments,",
    "start": "179070",
    "end": "180959"
  },
  {
    "text": "your dev,",
    "start": "180960",
    "end": "181960"
  },
  {
    "text": "your test,",
    "start": "183710",
    "end": "184710"
  },
  {
    "text": "and your prod environments,",
    "start": "186410",
    "end": "187970"
  },
  {
    "text": "can all be managed in your",
    "start": "189090",
    "end": "190769"
  },
  {
    "text": "infrastructure repo.",
    "start": "190770",
    "end": "191849"
  },
  {
    "text": "And then when you start deploying",
    "start": "193260",
    "end": "194639"
  },
  {
    "text": "services that your application",
    "start": "194640",
    "end": "196139"
  },
  {
    "text": "depends on things like a messaging",
    "start": "196140",
    "end": "197969"
  },
  {
    "text": "service that can",
    "start": "197970",
    "end": "199829"
  },
  {
    "text": "be managed as well in the",
    "start": "199830",
    "end": "201689"
  },
  {
    "text": "services repo.",
    "start": "201690",
    "end": "202690"
  },
  {
    "text": "And then the application itself,",
    "start": "207740",
    "end": "209569"
  },
  {
    "text": "you've got your application, the",
    "start": "209570",
    "end": "210979"
  },
  {
    "text": "source code continues to be managed",
    "start": "210980",
    "end": "213079"
  },
  {
    "text": "in the application repo.",
    "start": "213080",
    "end": "214759"
  },
  {
    "text": "So when you deploy that,",
    "start": "214760",
    "end": "216889"
  },
  {
    "text": "you've got your front-end and your",
    "start": "216890",
    "end": "218029"
  },
  {
    "text": "back-end.",
    "start": "218030",
    "end": "219030"
  },
  {
    "text": "That, again, is all managed",
    "start": "220670",
    "end": "222799"
  },
  {
    "text": "in Git.",
    "start": "222800",
    "end": "223969"
  },
  {
    "text": "And so rather than using the",
    "start": "223970",
    "end": "225619"
  },
  {
    "text": "different management consoles.",
    "start": "225620",
    "end": "227058"
  },
  {
    "text": "When you check in to Git.",
    "start": "229060",
    "end": "230650"
  },
  {
    "text": "You've got tools that are",
    "start": "232450",
    "end": "233528"
  },
  {
    "text": "automatically ensuring your get",
    "start": "233530",
    "end": "235089"
  },
  {
    "text": "environment manages",
    "start": "235090",
    "end": "237308"
  },
  {
    "text": "and matches your production",
    "start": "237310",
    "end": "238689"
  },
  {
    "text": "environment, so as changes are",
    "start": "238690",
    "end": "240579"
  },
  {
    "text": "made over here, they",
    "start": "240580",
    "end": "242439"
  },
  {
    "text": "get deployed and",
    "start": "242440",
    "end": "244929"
  },
  {
    "text": "mimicked over here so that they",
    "start": "244930",
    "end": "246519"
  },
  {
    "text": "match.",
    "start": "246520",
    "end": "247520"
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, one funny story is when",
    "start": "249270",
    "end": "251159"
  },
  {
    "text": "we were demoing this to",
    "start": "251160",
    "end": "252989"
  },
  {
    "text": "a customer, we started setting up",
    "start": "252990",
    "end": "254519"
  },
  {
    "text": "this whole environment.",
    "start": "254520",
    "end": "256259"
  },
  {
    "text": "And so we had our",
    "start": "256260",
    "end": "258328"
  },
  {
    "text": "Git repo, but get is pretty boring",
    "start": "258329",
    "end": "260278"
  },
  {
    "text": "to demo. No one wants to see a pull",
    "start": "260279",
    "end": "261897"
  },
  {
    "text": "request.",
    "start": "261899",
    "end": "263339"
  },
  {
    "text": "And we started showing OpenShift,",
    "start": "263340",
    "end": "265469"
  },
  {
    "text": "but no matter where we were, whether",
    "start": "265470",
    "end": "266999"
  },
  {
    "text": "we're on-prem in our one",
    "start": "267000",
    "end": "269129"
  },
  {
    "text": "cloud or another, cloud OpenShift",
    "start": "269130",
    "end": "271409"
  },
  {
    "text": "looked exactly the same.",
    "start": "271410",
    "end": "273269"
  },
  {
    "text": "So we started to pull up the",
    "start": "273270",
    "end": "274798"
  },
  {
    "text": "individual management consoles",
    "start": "274800",
    "end": "276839"
  },
  {
    "text": "and we realized we don't even have",
    "start": "276840",
    "end": "278609"
  },
  {
    "text": "access to the third party management",
    "start": "278610",
    "end": "280649"
  },
  {
    "text": "console or the team that was setting",
    "start": "280650",
    "end": "282479"
  },
  {
    "text": "this up was using a shared account",
    "start": "282480",
    "end": "284819"
  },
  {
    "text": "that had been locked down.",
    "start": "284820",
    "end": "286919"
  },
  {
    "text": "So even, even",
    "start": "286920",
    "end": "288839"
  },
  {
    "text": "demoing this stuff, we were",
    "start": "288840",
    "end": "290909"
  },
  {
    "text": "showing the value of GitOps because",
    "start": "290910",
    "end": "292799"
  },
  {
    "text": "it was",
    "start": "292800",
    "end": "293800"
  },
  {
    "text": "very secure in the fact that",
    "start": "294960",
    "end": "297059"
  },
  {
    "text": "we didn't even have access to show",
    "start": "297060",
    "end": "299219"
  },
  {
    "text": "those management consoles.",
    "start": "299220",
    "end": "300480"
  },
  {
    "text": "So GitOps is an approach that's",
    "start": "302500",
    "end": "304209"
  },
  {
    "text": "simple and consistent and secure",
    "start": "304210",
    "end": "306638"
  },
  {
    "text": "for managing your environments.",
    "start": "306640",
    "end": "308110"
  },
  {
    "text": "And you don't have to be like a",
    "start": "309400",
    "end": "311499"
  },
  {
    "text": "roller coaster, you can have boring",
    "start": "311500",
    "end": "313419"
  },
  {
    "text": "deployments across multicloud.",
    "start": "313420",
    "end": "316059"
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you. If you have any",
    "start": "316060",
    "end": "317259"
  },
  {
    "text": "questions, please drop us a line",
    "start": "317260",
    "end": "318759"
  },
  {
    "text": "below.",
    "start": "318760",
    "end": "319659"
  },
  {
    "text": "And if you want to see more videos",
    "start": "319660",
    "end": "321279"
  },
  {
    "text": "like this in the future, please like",
    "start": "321280",
    "end": "322899"
  },
  {
    "text": "and subscribe.",
    "start": "322900",
    "end": "323900"
  }
]